The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, June 29, 2004 				 NIIT offers 50% dividend
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, June 28: The NIIT group today announced a 50 per cent dividend to its 60,000 shareholders after registering a 20 per cent increase in revenues and a 330 per cent surge in operating profits for the 12-month period ending March 31, 2004.																								NIIT Ltd registered revenues of Rs 574.9 crore and an operating profit of Rs 23.8 crore. NIIT Technologies Ltd has registered a consolidated revenue of Rs 484.5 crore from its operations during the last financial year.																								The company also announced the completion of corporate restructuring with the creation of NIIT Technologies (NTL). The new company, which has been carved out of the NIIT group, will be listed on the stock markets by August-September.																								The capital has been structured in such a manner that a person holding 100 shares in NIIT Ltd (with a face value of Rs 10 each) will receive 50 shares of the demerged NIIT and 75 shares of NIIT Technologies (both with the face value of Rs 10 each). 
